==English==
===Proper Noun==
'''Low Countries''' (generally ''the Low Countries''')
{{wikipedia}}

#Historical region of ''de Nederlanden''.  The countries on low-lying land around the [[delta]] of the Rhine, Scheldt, and Meuse (Maas) rivers. The term is rare in modern usage because the region does accurately correspond with the sovereign states of The Netherlands, Belgium and Luxembourg, for which an alternate term, the [[Benelux]] was applied after World War II.